<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
The corruptions should be replaced by chaotic features, more similar to the old ZAngband mutations. <p>
Half of these is beneficial (e.g. increased stats, functional additional limbs, greater regeneration capabilities), the other half is detrimental (decreased stats, missing or not functional body parts, slower or no regeneration). 
</p>
<h3 id="head-22571c32c93f899f72749bdbd1078d9e5d7bb8da">Monsters with chaotic features</h3>
Chaotic monsters such as Dragonsnails, Gorps, Broos should obtain chaotic features, and the description of the monster should be changed accordingly. <p>
Example (from Arthur, but there are no orcs on Glorantha): Instead of 
<pre>He is one of the many weaker 'slave' orcs, often mistakenly known as a goblin.
</pre>you might also see 
<pre>He is one of the many weaker 'slave' orcs, often mistakenly known as a goblin.
He has a flailing spiked tentacle protruding from his back, and is confusing to look at.
</pre>
</p>
<p>
The creature would get an additional attack with the tentactle and a Confusion spell. 
</p>
